Fact 1: Rental Properties Generate Passive Income
Rental properties provide investors with monthly cash flow. Over time, rental income can cover mortgage payments and generate profit, especially in high-demand markets.

Fact 2: Real Estate Appreciates Over Time
Historically, real estate increases in value over the long term. This appreciation boosts an investorâ€™s equity and net worth, especially in growing urban or suburban areas.

Fact 3: Tax Benefits Are a Key Advantage
Real estate investors can deduct expenses like mortgage interest, insurance, repairs, depreciation, and property taxes. 1031 exchanges can also defer capital gains taxes when upgrading properties.
